posts.raw_content:
Stop tweeting and start using your position. You have ex-officio control of every federal agency and department. If any department head or agency head does not follow orders, you have the power to send in secret service agents, U.S. Marshals, HSI agents, or anyone you deem appropriate to enforce compliance through force in 20 minutes. You have the power to issue direct orders to any federal agent and any federal employee. 

Don’t tweet and expect people to do something. Pick up the phone and give direct orders to cabinet secretaries, agency directors, deputy directors, assistant directors, and etc. You can give orders to any ASAC, special agent, officer, or even probationary agent or officer. 

You can deputize anyone in the country as a federal agent, including all your followers, but you have to actually do something instead of tweet. 

If someone in the federal government doesn’t listen, they can be forcibly removed in 20 minutes by secret service agents.

You can send emissaries into any federal department or agent with a direct presidential order for all employees, including the cabinet secretary or agency head, to follow your emissary’s commands. You have the power to give your emissaries summary powers.

You can fire all generals and admirals from their commands, give orders directly to sub and destroyer commanders, and etc. You can call up anyone to active duty.

If a judge obstructs justice or criminally violates civil rights, it is your duty to arrest them. They don't need to be impeached. They can be arrested on the spot for a witnessed felony without an indictment. Any judge who tries to release a judge or tries to dismiss charges can be arrested in the courtroom for obstruction of justice. You control all federal agents and can order them to ignore illegal court orders and you can fire federal agents on the spot.

Stop thinking you don’t have the power. The AG, U.S. Marshal, Secret Service Director, DHS Secretary, and the FBI Director answer to you and you can have them removed and arrested in 20 minutes if they don’t carry out your orders.

posts.raw_content: Nothing seemed to go right today. I’m based in Florida and just paid my property taxes, which pretty much wiped out my savings. Now the AC has died, and since I’m doing my part to raise a growing family, my one-year-old will need to sleep uncomfortably for a few days while I figure out what to do. I’m not going to whine about it, and I’m not getting on welfare. I’ll handle it one way or another. I fed the family today, so that was great though I had a can of tuna myself, not so great. But at the end of the day, I can come here and see that some of us are still trying to make a difference, and it gives me hope that maybe we can fix this country, because damn… things are rough! Stay strong Pedes.
